Steps :
1. Create a .gitignore_global file in root directory in Mac terminal.
    touch ~/.gitignore_global
    
2. Open file in terminal
    open ~/.gitignore_global
    
3. Keep files name in following manner which you want to ignore 
    # Ignorable files
    .classpath
    .project
    .settings
    suite.xml
    
4. Keep directories name in following manner which you want to ignore 
    #directories
    selionFiles
    bin
    test-output
    
5. save.

6. git config --global core.excludesfile ~/.gitignore_global

7. You are done, check by
    git status 
    Note: you won't find files mentioned in .gitignore_global either tracked or untracked.
